¼ cup olive oil
1 clove Garlic
2 sprig Rosemary
pinch Chilli Flakes
1 packet Cow's Milk Feta
1 carrot
1 cucumber
1 Sourdough Loaf
1 packet coppa di parma
1 packet Pitted Mixed Olives
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish

• Finely chop garlic. Pick rosemary leaves (see ingredients).
• To a small microwave-safe bowl, add the olive oil, garlic, rosemary and a pinch of chilli flakes (if using). Microwave until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Set aside and allow to cool completely

• While the garlic oil is cooling, cut cow's milk feta into bite-sized chunks.
• Arrange in an airtight container.
• When the garlic oil is completely cool, pour over the feta to cover. Store in the fridge until needed.

• Slice carrot and cucumber into sticks.
• Slice the sourdough loaf into 4 even slices. Toast or grill sourdough to your liking.

• On a serving board, place marinated feta, coppa di parma, pitted mixed olives, chargrilled capsicum relish, sourdough and veggie sticks. Enjoy!